core.User: the built-in people directory (real, queryable)

ref[core.User] was a stub — the picker fell back to a raw id input. core.User
is now a real, read-only entity projected from the identity registry: the
record endpoints serve it from the actor directory instead of the engine.

- GET /api/records/core.User and POST /api/query/core.User return the actors
  (id/name/role/type), filtered by a case-insensitive search over id and role,
  capped by limit.
- GET /api/records/core.User/{id} resolves one actor for label display.
- The web ref picker and the read-mode ref label now treat core.User like any
  entity, so assignee/reporter fields are a search-as-you-type people picker
  that scales to 150k users instead of a load-everything combobox.

Read-only by design: users are created through register/invite, not the record
API. Verified by a directory test (list, search by id, search by role, get one)
and live in the browser (typing in the assignee field lists the directory).
